Let $R$ be the rectangle in the Cartesian plane with vertices at $(0,0)$, $(2,0)$, $(2,1)$, and $(0,1)$. $R$ can be divided into two unit squares, as shown. 
\begin{asy}
import olympiad;
import cse5;
defaultpen(white);
size(100);
size(120); defaultpen(linewidth(0.7)); 
draw(origin--(2,0)--(2,1)--(0,1)--cycle^^(1,0)--(1,1));
\end{asy}
\\
 Pro selects a point $P$ at random in the interior of $R$. Find the probability that the line through $P$ with slope $\frac{1}{2}$ will pass through both unit squares.
